    "text": "Cockles and mussels – Cockles and mussels\nIn Dublin’s fair city, wo die Mädels so pretty, da sah ich zum ersten Mal Molly Malone. Als sie schob ihren Karren durch Straßen und Gassen, sie rief: cockles and mussels alive alive ho. Refrain: Alive alive ho, alive alive ho II: Crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho :II\nCockels and mussels\nShe was a fishmonger and sure t’was no wonder, for so where her father and mother before and they both wheeled their barrows through streets broad and narrow crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho Refrain: Alive alive ho, alive alive ho II: Crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho :II She died of a fever and no one could save her and that was the end of sweet Molly Malone, but her ghost wheels the barrow through streets broad and narrow crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho Refrain: Alive alive ho, alive alive ho II: Crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho :II\nCockels and mussels\nJa so war mein Leben, mal holprig, mal eben, ich war so verliebt in die Molly Malone. Als sie schob ihren Karren mit Holpern und Knarrren, sie rief: cockles and mussels alive alive ho.\nRefrain: Alive alive ho, alive alive ho II: Crying cockles and mussels alive alive ho :II\nInstrumentalsolo"
